Daniel Zambukeri was sentenced to an effective life
imprisonment by the Limpopo High Court sitting in Thohoyandou for murder.The 33-year-old Zambukeri was found guilty for his role
in the brutal murder of his elder brother's wife, Hlayisani Preshia Hlongwani,
aged 26.Limpopo cops spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the
heavy jail term emanated from an incident which took place on  17 April 2017 when the accused  promised to accompany the deceased from
